#. <section class="sutta" id="sn34.55"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn34.55:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 34"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 34"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn34.55:0.2"
msgid "1. Jhānavagga"
msgstr "1. Absorption"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 55. Sātaccamūlakasappāyakārīsutta → sākaccasappāyakārīsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn34.55:0.3"
msgid "55. Sātaccamūlakasappāyakārīsutta"
msgstr "55. Persistence and What’s Conducive"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.278"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn34.55:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.2"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, jhāyī."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four meditators."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī hoti, na samādhismiṃ "
"sappāyakārī."
msgstr ""
"One meditator is skilled in practicing persistently for immersion but not in "
"doing what’s conducive to it."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ sappāyakārī hoti, na "
"samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī."
msgstr ""
"One meditator is skilled in doing what’s conducive to immersion but not in "
"practicing persistently for it."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.6"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī neva samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī hoti, na ca "
"samādhismiṃ sappāyakārī."
msgstr ""
"One meditator is skilled neither in practicing persistently for immersion "
"nor in doing what’s conducive to it."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.7"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco jhāyī samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī ca hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ sappāyakārī ca."
msgstr ""
"One meditator is skilled both in practicing persistently for immersion and "
"in doing what’s conducive to it."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.8"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī ca hoti samādhismiṃ "
"sappāyakārī ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca mokkho ca "
"uttamo ca pavaro ca."
msgstr ""
"Of these, the meditator skilled both in practicing persistently for "
"immersion and in doing what’s conducive to it is the foremost, best, "
"leading, highest, and finest of the four."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gavā khīraṃ, khīramhā dadhi, dadhimhā navanītaṃ, "
"navanītamhā sappi, sappimhā sappimaṇḍo tatra aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"From a cow comes milk, from milk comes curds, from curds come butter, from "
"butter comes ghee, and from ghee comes cream of ghee. And the cream of ghee "
"is said to be the best of these."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.10"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ jhāyī samādhismiṃ sātaccakārī ca hoti, "
"samādhismiṃ sappāyakārī ca ayaṃ imesaṃ catunnaṃ jhāyīnaṃ aggo ca seṭṭho ca "
"mokkho ca uttamo ca pavaro cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, the meditator skilled both in practicing persistently for "
"immersion and in doing what’s conducive to it is the foremost, best, "
"leading, highest, and finest of the four.”"

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.11"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn34.55:1.12"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn34.55:1.13"
msgid "Pañcapaññāsamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn34.55:1.14"
msgid "(Yathā pañcapaññāsaṃ veyyākaraṇāni honti tathā vitthāretabbāni.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn34.55:1.15"
msgid "Khandhavaggo tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn34.55:2.1"
msgid "Samādhi samāpatti ṭhiti ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:2.2"
msgid "Vuṭṭhānaṃ kallitārammaṇena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:2.3"
msgid "Gocarā abhinīhāro sakkacca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:2.4"
msgid "Sātacca athopi sappāyanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn34.55:2.5"
msgid "Jhānasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Absorption are complete."

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.279"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.1"
msgid "Khandha rādhasaṃyuttañca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
#. VAR: diṭṭhiokkanta → okkanti (sabbattha)
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.2"
msgid "diṭṭhiokkanta uppādā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.3"
msgid "Kilesa sāriputtā ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.4"
msgid "nāgā supaṇṇa gandhabbā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.5"
msgid "Valāha vacchajhānanti,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.6"
msgid "khandhavaggamhi terasāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "sn34.55:3.7"
msgid "Khandhavaggasaṃyuttapāḷi niṭṭhitā."
msgstr "The Book of the Aggregates is finished."
